      <section id="varieties" class="sec-padding">
        <h3 class="section-heading">VARIETIES</h3>
        <div class="sec-content-div flexible">
          <div class="tile">
            <img src="c:\HTML\Landing Page\bhagwa.webp" alt="photo of amber apples" />
            <h4>Bhagwa</h4>
            <p>
              Also known as Shendria or Sinduri, Astagandha and Kesar. This is a selection from F2 population of the cross Ganesh x Gulesha Red. Fruits are attractive glossy red rind. Arils are blood red in colour. It is soft seeded variety.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="tile">
            <img
              src="c:\HTML\Landing Page\arkta.webp"
              alt="photo of american trel apples"
            />
            <h4>Arakta</h4>
            <p>
              The fruits are smaller than Ganesh variety having dark red coloured arils with soft seeds.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="tile">
            <img src="c:\HTML\Landing Page\maridula.webp" alt="photo of red delicious apple" />
            <h4>Mridula</h4>
            <p>
              This variety has all the characters of the Ganesh variety except the arils are dark red in colour. The colour of the arils in 'Ambe' bahar and 'Mrig' bahar is dark red in colour while it is pink during the 'Hasta' bahar. The average fruit weight is 250-300 grams.

            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="tile">
            <img src="c:\HTML\Landing Page\dholka.webp" alt="photo of Maharaej apples" />
            <h4>Dholka</h4>
            <p>
              Fruits large, rind yellowish red with pinkish white aril. It is a popular cultivar of Gujarat. 

            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="tile">
            <img src="c:\HTML\Landing Page\ganesh.webp" alt="photo of Hazratbael apples" />
            <h4>Ganesh</h4>
            <p>
              This variety is developed by selection method (selction from Alandi). It is a prolific bearer, fruit are medium sized with yellow, smooth and red tinge. Seeds are soft with pinkish aril. Juice tastes sweet. It is the commercial cultivar of Maharashtra. The average yield ranges from 8-10 kg per tree.

            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="tile">
            <img src="c:\HTML\Landing Page\ruby.webp" alt="photo of Golden Delicious apples" />
            <h4>Ruby</h4>
            <p>
              This variety is developed at IIHR, Bangalore. The mature fruits resemble cultivar 'Ganesh' with respect to shape and size. However, the rind of this variety is reddish brown with green streaks containing red bold arils. The fruit weighs 270 g with an average yield of 16-18 tonnes/ha. 

            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
